CAPE TOWN, South Africa (AP) — India was 75-2 at lunch on the opening day of the decisive final test against South Africa on Tuesday to stage a mini-recovery after losing early wickets at Newlands.Openers KL Rahul and Mayank Agarwal were out in the space of six balls and India was 33-2 before captain Virat Kohli and Cheteshwar Pujara came together and took the tourists to lunch.Kohli, who was back after missing the second test with injury, was 15 not out. Pujara was 26 not out. India chose to bat first in Cape Town but encountered trouble on the first morning, when cloudy skies aided South Africa’s pace bowlers.Rahul was caught behind off Duanne Olivier for 12 and Mayank fell in the next over for 15 to Kagiso Rabada.India made two changes for the finale of the series, which is at 1-1 after the tourists won the opening test and South Africa hit back in the second.ADVERTISEMENTKohli was back in after an upper back spasm ruled him out of the second test in Johannesburg on the morning the game started. India also called in seamer Umesh Yadav to replace Mohammed Siraj, who has an injury.South Africa selected an unchanged team after putting itself back in contention in the series.India, the top-ranked team in the world, has never won a test series in South Africa and is seeking that piece of history on its eighth test tour to the country.___More AP cricket: https://apnews.com/hub/cricket and https://twitter.com/AP_Sports